node.title: Two healthcare workers who visited aged care homes in Adelaide test positive to COVID-19
node.alt: An elderly man crosses his hands.
node.description: Two healthcare workers who provided care at a number of residential aged care facilities in Adelaide test positive to COVID-19. Authorities are contacting impacted sites.
node.content: ["South Australia has recorded 12 new cases of COVID-19, including two healthcare workers who have visited and provided care at a number of residential aged care homes in Adelaide.", "The cases include four women and four men aged between 20 and 60 and four children under 12.", "In a statement, SA Health said impacted aged care sites were being contacted and supported to implement \"additional infection control measures\" while testing of residents and staff was being undertaken.", "Authorities have not yet publicly released details of which aged care facilities are affected.", "The state's exposure sites list has also not yet been updated for the day.", "SA Health said of the new cases, five people acquired COVID-19\u00a0in South Australia, and are known contacts of a positive case.", "One person acquired it interstate.", "Six acquired the virus within Australia, but\u00a0investigations into the source of their infections are\u00a0still ongoing.", "More to come.\u00a0"]
